HEADWORD: Incapacious
<hw>In`ca*pa"cious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>capacious</ets>: cf. L. <ets>incapax</ets>
incapable.]</ety> <def>Not capacious; narrow; small; weak or foolish;
<as>as, an <ex>incapacious</ex> soul</as>.</def> <au>Bp. Burnet.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>In`ca*pa"cious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
